Hello, and welcome back to Line Sheet. Intrepid channel checker Sarah
=E2=80=9CSShapiro@puck.news=E2=80=9D Shapiro is here with the week that was=
 in retail, including The White Lotus=E2=80=99s nutso flood of brand collab=
orations. (They definitely took the Barbie approach.) Up top, Sarah also pr=
ovides a snapshot of consumer spending habits right now, and explains why y=
ou=E2=80=99re suddenly seeing Shoreditch-based fashion brand Aligne everywh=
ere these days. (It=E2=80=99s not only
because Gabby Katz is the publicist.) And I=E2=80=99ve got some deal detail=
s from Tapestry=E2=80=99s sale of Stuart Weitzman to Caleres, which is set =
to close this summer.

By the time you read this, I=E2=80=99ll be on a plane to New York, where I=
=E2=80=99m interviewing Alex Mill chairman and all-around legend Mickey Dre=
xler at Columbia Business School=E2=80=99s Retail & Luxury Goods Club Confe=
rence on Saturday morning. (If you=E2=80=99re there, please don=E2=80=99t h=
esitate to say hi while waiting to kiss
Mickey=E2=80=99s ring.) After this, it=E2=80=99s over to London, Milan, and=
=E2=80=A6 Paris! How great. Let=E2=80=99s hang.

Mentioned in this issue: Christian Louboutin, Ralph Lauren, The Row, Beyonc=
=C3=A9, Aligne, Ginny Seymour, Olivia Muniak, Stuart Weitzman, Tapestry, Jo=
anne Crevoiserat, Miu Miu, Petit Bateau, Zara, Gap, Reformation, Lezio Lope=
s, The White Lotus, Parker Posey,
Net-a-Porter, Mytheresa, and many more=E2=80=A6

=E2=80=8A

